The paper deals with the problem of finding heavy hitters in data streams, which is a classic problem in the area of data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The algorithm proposed in the paper involves probabilistic techniques and analysis, which are common in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the space and time complexity of the algorithm, which is relevant to the area of computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper proposes a new chaining argument, which may have applications in other areas of computer science, such as cryptography or information security (cs.SI).
